article.headline: Howard 81, Coppin St 66
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Darryl Hudson came off the bench to score 18 points and grab 10 rebounds as Howard defeated Coppin State 81-66 on Saturday. Louis Ford added 17 points for Howard (4-20, 3-12 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), while Darek Mitchell scored 12 points, and Will Gant had 11. It was the second straight win for the Bison, which had not won consecutive games since December 2004. Tywain McKee led Coppin State (11-16, 11-5 MEAC) with 19 points, and Darryl Proctor added 18. Howard jumped out to an early lead and made it 38-21 at the half. They never let the Eagles get within single digits. The Bison shot 12-of-19 in the second half, including 5-of-6 from 3-point range. Ford, Gant and Mitchell combined for 11 3-pointers among them. ^
